8 A Concurrent Resolution commending and congratulating
the United States of America's Olympic national
9 hockey teams for winning gold medals at the XXV
Winter Olympic Games.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, outstanding athletic achievements reflect great credit
13 upon our nation; and
14 WHEREAS, the Olympic Games are considered the world's preeminent
15 international sporting event; and
16 WHEREAS, the United States of America's men's and women's
17 national hockey teams each achieved victory against Canada; and
18 WHEREAS, both contests were decided in overtime by golden goal,
19 demonstrating exceptional skill, resolve, and competitive
20 excellence; and
21 WHEREAS, these victories further affirm the strength and
22 prominence of American hockey and establish the United States of
23 America as the preeminent world power in the sport; and
24
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1020 Page 1

1 WHEREAS, the players, coaches, and support personnel of both
2 teams have distinguished themselves as exemplary representatives of
3 the United States of America and serve as an inspiration to athletes
4 throughout Oklahoma and the nation.
5 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
6 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
7 CONCURRING THEREIN:
8 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the Oklahoma
9 State Senate commend and congratulate the United States of America's
10 men's and women's national hockey teams for their gold medal
11 victories and for the exemplary manner in which they represented the
12 United States of America at the XXV Winter Olympic Games.
13 THAT copies of this Resolution be transmitted and delivered to
14 the Secretary of State, USA Hockey, appropriate representatives of
15 the men's and women's national hockey teams, and to the United
16 States Olympic & Paralympic Committee.
